<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-3012] Timing problems in NamedPipe implementation due to unnecessary open/close</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-3012</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Under some load, clients connecting to especially a single pipe server will experience some connection problems due to frequent close &amp;amp; reopen of the server pipe. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This ia a) unnecessary, and it is b) caused by the default timeouts on the server side, which are unnecessarily short. The short server timeouts are a leftover from the days before using the overlapped method - now &lt;tt&gt;INFINITE&lt;/tt&gt; should do a better job on the server side.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
